Key Match Events: Victor Wembanyama finished with 12 points, eight rebounds, two assists, four steals and three blocks while shooting 4/13 from the field in 32 minutes.
The Spurs won by a score of 118-105 to improve to 4-5 in their first nine games.
Post-Match Reflections: Many NBA fans reacted to Victor Wembanyama's performance, expressing disappointment in his shooting and overall play.
Some fans noted that Deandre Ayton dominated Wembanyama in the first half, suggesting that Wembanyama's performance has been off this season possibly due to exhaustion from the Olympics.
